    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>to a bowl with the<strong> grated carrot</strong>, <strong>sliced cucumber</strong>,<strong> tomato wedges</strong>, <strong>crunchy pitta</strong> and most of the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>mint</strong> and <strong>dill</strong> (save some for garnish!)</p><p>Add 1/2 tbsp [3/4 tbsp] [1 tbsp] <strong>olive oil</strong> and the juice<strong> </strong>from the <strong>remaining lemon </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a gentle mix up – this is your <strong>crunchy pitta salad</strong></p>",
